entries.meaning: (snooker) An instance of reracking the balls to restart a frame.

verbs.description: rerack (third-person singular simple present reracks, present participle reracking, simple past and past participle reracked)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To place back in a rack.
examples: Please rerack the weights before you leave the gym.

entries.meaning: (transitive, billiards, snooker, pool) To rack (the balls) again, as when preparing for a new game.
